description: {"blocks":[{"key":"8tr3a","text":"MycoFluor™ Mycoplasma Detection produces a fast and simple fluorescence microscopic assay that identifies mycoplasma infection in cell cultures. In order to detect mycoplasma, the fluorescent MycoFluor™ reagent is added to the culture medium, with or without cells, and the sample becomes stained and examined under a fluorescence microscope.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"e5bn5","text":"Reagents Needed: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":17}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5pm4s","text":"MycoFluor Mycoplasma Detection Kit (M-7006) ","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2fvsr","text":"Microcentrifuge tubes ","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"38h3m","text":"Microscope slides","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7jigo","text":"Clear coverslips ","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working.

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"5r5nq","text":"Take about 4mL of cell medium directly form the culture dish in which the cells have been growing centrifuge the sample at 1300 x g for 10min to pellet any cells and debris","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dv3ln","text":"Carefully transfer 1mL of supernatant into labeled microcentrifuge tubes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3bsju","text":"Centrifuge the microcentrifuge tubes at 12,500 x g for 15 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9vs8a","text":"Carefully remove and discard 0.5mL of supernatant, leaving behind 0.5mL of medium in the tube. Resuspend any pellet that may have formed using this 0.5mL of medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a7lms","text":"Add 26µL of 20X concentrated MycoFluor reagent to 0.5mL of the medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7n96r","text":"Pipet 10µL of the stained medium onto a clean microscope slide and cover with a clean coverslip.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"913jq","text":"Seal the slide using quick dry clear nail polish topcoat by covering all sides of the coverslip.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"f855d","text":"Generating positive controls for the testing of culture media","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b4r1d","text":"a. Pipet 5µL of the mycoplasma MORFS stock suspension on a clean, labeled microscope slide","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9pdt2","text":"b. Add 5µL of stained medium to the slide ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bu430","text":"c. Cover with clear coverslip and seal using quick dry topcoat nail polish. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1qkhn","text":"Image the positive controls and compare to the samples that have not been spiked with MORFS ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bej99","text":"Prepare the microscope with a near ultraviolet fluorescence filter (Excitation at 365nm and either bandpass 450nm ± 30nm or longpass \u003e400nm emission filter)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3agpe","text":"For optimum result, a 100X oil immersion objective is suggested but a 60X oil immersion objective will also work","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ih8j","text":"First look at the control slide spiked with MORFS to get an idea what it should look like. Then examine the test slide for extranuclear blue fluorescence.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: MycoFluor Mycoplasma Detection
